<h2 class="aboutHead">BUYER PROTECTION POLICY - Farmgate Nigeria</h2>
<p><i>Last Updated: [07/12/2025]</i></p>
<p>
    Farmgate Nigeria is committed to ensuring safe, transparent, and trustworthy transactions for all buyers on 
    our platform. This Buyer Protection Policy explains the safeguards we put in place and the rights of buyers 
    who use our services. 
</p>

<h2 class="aboutHead">1. Safe Transactions</h2>
<h3>Farmgate Nigeria prioritizes secure and verified transactions by:</h3>
Offering agent-mediated transactions between buyers and sellers.<br>
Requiring sellers to list realistic prices.<br>
Ensuring that sellers comply with platform quality and honesty standards.

<h2 class="aboutHead">2. Verified Sellers</h2>
<h3>Buyers have the right to:</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Request verification of any seller through Farmgate Nigeria.</li>
    <li>Contact any of our admins for confirmation of legitimacy.</li>
    <li>Refuse to engage with any seller who cannot be verified.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="aboutHead">3. Quality Assurance</h2>
<h3>To protect buyers:</h3>
All produce must match the description provided by the seller.
If Farmgate Nigeria agents are involved, they will inspect produce to confirm quality and quantity before delivery.
If the delivered product significantly differs from what was promised, buyers may report the issue for review.

<h2 class="aboutHead">4. Payment Protection</h2>
<h3>Farmgate Nigeria strongly promotes payment upon delivery, which protects buyers by ensuring that:</h3>
<p>
    Payment is only made after produce has been verified.<br>
    No buyer is required to pay upfront unless an officially approved process is in place.<br>
    Buyers should never send money to unofficial accounts or unknown individuals.<br>
</p>


<h2 class="aboutHead">5. Fraud Prevention Measures</h2>
<h3>Buyers are protected through the following:</h3>
<p>
    Farmgate Nigeria will never call from undocumented numbers.<br>
    We will never ask buyers to release payment before verification is completed.<br>
    Buyers are encouraged to report any suspicious activity immediately. 
</p>


<h2 class="aboutHead">6. Dispute Resolution</h2>
<h3>If a disagreement arises:</h3>
<p>
    Buyers may file a complaint through our official channels.<br>
    Farmgate Nigeria will mediate disputes between buyers and sellers.<br>
    Resolutions may include verification, replacement, refunds through the seller, or account actions.
</p>


<h2 class="aboutHead">7. Right to Safe Access</h2>
<h3>Buyers have the right to:</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Transparent information</li>
    <li>Fair pricing</li>
    <li>Verified seller profiles</li>
    <li>Honest representation of produce</li>
    <li>Safe meeting points, facilitated by agents where necessary</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="aboutHead">8. Limitations</h2>
<h3>While Farmgate Nigeria provides extensive safeguards, we cannot:</h3>
<p>
    Guarantee transactions conducted outside the platform<br>
    Protect buyers who ignore verification processes<br>
    Take responsibility for seller misrepresentation if Farmgate Nigeria was not involved in the transaction
</p>


